                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p> RIKINGHALE, &amp;c. Final concord, <origDate when="1207">Mich. 9 K. John</origDate>, by which 
                  <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename>, son of <persName>
                              <forename>William</forename> de <surname>Costantin</surname>
                           </persName></persName>, 
                  acknowledges that no acres of land in <placeName key="place_105466">Rickinghall (Rikingehale)</placeName> is the right of 
                  <persName>
                           <forename>Samson</forename>, the abbot</persName>, and <orgName key="org_104015">church of St. Edmund</orgName>, 
                  for which concession the abbot re-granted to the said John 41 acres of the said land, 
                  (in several defined portions) also other land, and a messuage in the wood of 
                  '<placeName type="minor">Cumbhage</placeName>,' at an annual rent of 12d.
                     </p>
